                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d736">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/9076</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Valencia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Valencia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-28T13:00:00-04:30"
                            >March 28, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Ugarte<note n="48" xml:id="d736fn48">Custodian of American Embassy premises
                        at Madrid.</note> has just telephoned to report that Madrid was surrendered
                    this morning by the National Defense Council whose members have all departed
                    except Besteiro. The entry of the Nationalist troops is expected this afternoon
                    but the city is already bedecked with Nationalist flags. There are no disorders
                    and all Americans are believed safe.</p>
                <p>Valencia quiet.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
